The GMP manual says that after writing the limbs via the pointer returned by mpz_limbs_write, you should call mpz_limbs_finish(z, n), where n is the number of limbs. So the code should be:

mpz_limbs_finish(out->get_mpz_t(), limb_size);

Therefore, the missing line after the loop is mpz_limbs_finish(out->get_mpz_t(), limb_size); So the TODO comment is indicating that this line is missing.
